## Adding a new program

Use the plugin:

```
/pgas-new-program
```

The plugin's `/pgas-new-program` command detects this repo as a pgas
consumer, finds the `[pgas-plugin:*-registry]` markers in
`server/index.ts`, asks for the program name, and diff-and-confirms the
scaffold before writing.

## Cutting a release

Per `simodelne/pgas`/CONSUMER-VERSIONING-CONTRACT.md:

1. Bump `package.json` version.
2. If minor or major bump: run `/pgas:architecture-doc` to generate
   `audit/ARCHITECTURE-{{CONSUMER_NAME}}-v<X.Y.0>.md`.
3. Run `/pgas:5-fm-audit` — verify all five failure modes stay closed.
4. Open release PR; CI runs the same checks.
5. After merge, tag + push: `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push --tags`.
6. The `publish.yml` workflow publishes to GitHub Packages and
   nudges (warn-only) if the architecture doc is missing.

